---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dream Home | Seba Sepulveda">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-3xl py-16">
    <a href="/projects" class="mb-8 inline-block text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-yellow-400 transition-colors">
      &lt;- Back to projects
    </a>

    <header class="mb-10">
      <div class="mb-3 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
        <span class="rounded-full border border-emerald-500/30 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-emerald-400">Active</span>
        <span class="rounded-full border border-emerald-500/30 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-emerald-400">Real estate</span>
        <span class="rounded-full border border-emerald-500/30 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs text-emerald-400">Chile</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Dream Home</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300">
        A mortgage and property analysis app for people evaluating home purchases in Chile, where UF values, down payment, credit capacity and property comparison all matter at the same time.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Why it exists</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Buying a home usually starts in spreadsheets: income assumptions, down payment, mortgage capacity, UF values, candidate properties and follow-up notes live in separate places.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-300">
        Dream Home turns that scattered workflow into a product experience for comparing properties, understanding affordability scenarios and keeping useful decision data together.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">What it does</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
        <li>Simulates mortgage capacity and purchase scenarios.</li>
        <li>Uses UF-aware calculations for the Chilean real estate context.</li>
        <li>Stores and compares candidate properties.</li>
        <li>Supports maps, geocoding and location review.</li>
        <li>Tracks quotations and exports property data for follow-up.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Technical shape</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Application</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Next.js, TypeScript, React, Tailwind CSS and component-driven product flows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Financial model</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Affordability simulation, target price, down payment, credit needs and UF service integration.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Property workflow</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Property lists, details, quotations, local storage and export schemas.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-800 p-4">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Maps</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Address autocomplete, geocoding, coordinates validation and map-based review.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Live app</h2>
      <a
        href="https://dream-home-pi.vercel.app/"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-block rounded-lg border border-emerald-500/40 px-4 py-2 text-sm text-emerald-300 hover:bg-emerald-500/10 transition-colors"
      >
        Open Dream Home on Vercel
      </a>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-500">
        Deployed on Vercel. This page links to the public app.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Planned articles</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-300">
        <li>Dream Home: turning Chilean home buying math into a product.</li>
        <li>From spreadsheet to real estate product: lessons from Dream Home.</li>
        <li>Using maps and geocoding as product infrastructure.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
